vice of contemporary capitalism, blurring the line between creativity and entrepreneurship, and challenging us to imagine how a noncommodified musical practice might be possible in today’s world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMusic and technologyzUnited States. 0aMusic entrepreneurshipzUnited States. 0aMusic tradezUnited States. 0aMusicxEconomic aspectszUnited States. 0aNeoliberalismzUnited States. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aUnited States.  acapitalism.  aclassical music.  acorporations.  aentrepreneurship.  aindividualism.  alabor.  amarket logic.  amodernism.  aneoliberalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226640372423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226640372.jpg  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles